{
  "texts": [
    "Maybe most importantly of all, investing in computer skills allows expanding the solution space of possible study designs, thereby opening new research vistas that are simply not available to researchers who do not have the required skills.",
    "When doing jobs such as building experiments with tens or hundreds of trials, or analyzing data from an eye-tracker that records a thousand samples per second, it is often not an effective use of time to approach this work manually.",
    "For these and many other jobs, a good piece of code can vastly improve the effectiveness and efficiency of one's research compared to performing them manually and also reduces the potential for mistakes to sneak in.",
    "Our strong recommendation therefore is for the reader to consider learning to program.",
    "What do we mean when we say \"learn how to program\"?"
  ]
}